<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Lincoln or Liverpool will host Leicester or Arsenal in the Fourth Round of the Carabao Cup.</p>

<p>Leyton Orient or Tottenham will face Chelsea or Barnsley, with the possibility raised of Jose Mourinho taking on his former club. </p>

<p>Meanwhile, if Manchester United manage to get past Luton they will play Preston or Brighton </p>

<p>The ties for this round will be played in the week commencing September 28. </p>

<p>Liverpool could face Arsenal and Tottenham may play Chelsea in Carabao Cup fourth roundL</p>

<p>Liverpool and Arsenal drew 5-5 in an enthralling encounter in the fourth round last season</p>

<p>Liverpool and Arsenal met at this stage of the competition last season, with the game ending in a 5-5 draw and Jurgen Klopp's side prevailing on penalties. </p>

<p>Other ties see holders Manchester City or Bournemouth travelling to take on Millwall or Burnley. </p>

<p>Fleetwood or Everton will host West Ham or Hull. West Brom or Brentford will be up against Sheffield Wednesday.</p>

<p>Elsewhere, Bristol City or Aston Villa will play Stoke or Gillingham. Newport County or Watford will play Morecambe or Newcastle.  </p>

<p>Lincoln City or Liverpool v Leicester City or Arsenal</p>

<p>Millwall or Burnley v Manchester City or Bournemouth</p>

<p>West Brom or Brentford v Fulham or Sheffield Wednesday</p>

<p>Fleetwood Town or Everton v West Ham or Hull</p>

<p>Bristol City or Aston Villa v Stoke or Gillingham</p>

<p>Leyton Orient or Tottenham v Chelsea or Barnsley</p>

<p>Newport County or Watford v Morecambe or Newcastle</p>

<p>Preston or Brighton v Luton or Manchester United </p>
